#TAUTOLOGY CHECKER

Tautology checker is program which checks whether a given Statement is a tautology or not.
Valid logical operators are '|', '&' and '!'

* Ruby version - (2.2.2)

## How to Run?

    $ git clone https://github.com/sikar/TautologyChecker.git

    $ cd TautologyChecker

    $ bundle

    $ ruby lib/app.rb


## How to Test?

    $ cd TautologyChecker
    $ rspec spec

## Example

Do enter the no. of propositional statements you want to check?
3
Enter the propositional statement. Once you enter a propositional statement , press `Enter`:
(a & (!b | b)) | (!a & (!b | b))
!a & !b
a & (b | c)

Results for Statements checked for Tautology :
True

Results for Statements checked for Tautology :
False

Results for Statements checked for Tautology :
False
